        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-21T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="1275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/2–2045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-21T16:00:00-04:00">February 21, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. ReEmbs 240, February 20. Please inform the Prime Minister personally of the
                    Secretary General’s somewhat casual indication of <pb facs="1315" n="1303" xml:id="pg_1303"/> further delay. Department suggests that the Prime
                    Minister should, in Turkey’s best interest, see to it that Turkey’s signature of
                    the Mutual Aid Agreement is not delayed by the absence from Ankara of one or two
                    officials. The matter is too important to be left dangling, particularly at this
                    time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
